#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:7
msgid "Blender Internationalization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:9
msgid ""
"From version 2.60, Blender supports international fonts and a range of "
"language options for the Interface and Tooltips. To enable it, open the "
"*User Preferences* window, *System* tab, and toggle the *International "
"Fonts* option in the bottom right-hand corner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:14
msgid "This displays three new settings:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:19
msgid "Enabling international fonts in the User Preferences window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:22
msgid "Language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:23
msgid "drop-down menu where you can select your preferred language."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:24
msgid "Interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:25
msgid "to translate the User Interface itself (e.g. controls and menus)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:28
msgid "Tooltips"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:27
msgid "to translate tooltips."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:32
msgid ""
"Blender with the Russian language enabled for the Interface and Tooltips."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:35
msgid ""
"Blender refreshes the screen after selecting Interface or Tooltips (or both)"
" to show the new language. Note that some language translations are not yet "
"complete. The progress of each translation is indicated in the drop-down "
"menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/basics/interface/internationalization.rst:42
msgid ""
"Since the majority of tutorials are done with an English User Interface, it "
"may be useful to keep the User Interface in English and only translate the "
"tooltips, but it's important to note that the Blender User Interface "
"translation, user manuals translation and development, together with "
"community work, could develop a strong Blender user base, promoting Blender "
"and localized Blender jobs!"
msgstr ""
